# harness/.policy_allow.local — sample
#
# Copy this file to `.policy_allow.local` (gitignored via *.local) and list
# base command names, one per line, that you want the harness to allow
# without consulting the LLM policy judge. Commands listed here still go
# through the sensitive-command validators (pkill/chmod/rm/gh).
#
# The default policy denies anything not in harness/security.py::ALLOWED_COMMANDS.
# Use this file when you need a new dev tool allowed locally without editing
# security.py (which would require a code review + PR).
#
# Example:
#   rg
#   fd
#   bat
#   just
